# Dynamic Config First â€” no hardcoded admin lists

This codebase has accumulated multiple violations where a React
component hand-types a list of options that an admin should be able
to edit (premium roles, premium contexts, DB column suggestions,
role-visibility rules, package-is-premium checks, user-type labels,
PDF synthetic fields, etc.). The skill at
[`.cursor/skills/dynamic-config-first/SKILL.md`](mdc:.cursor/skills/dynamic-config-first/SKILL.md)
catalogues every known violation and the migration path for each.

If your task touches **any** of the following, STOP and read the
skill **before** writing code:

- Adding ANY new dropdown / checkbox group / radio group in an
  admin editor (`components/admin/**`)
- Adding a new value to `PREMIUM_ROLE_OPTIONS`, `PREMIUM_CONTEXT_OPTIONS`,
  `DB_COLUMN_OPTIONS`, `COLUMN_TO_SUGGESTED_ROLE`, or any sibling
  array in `EditPackageFieldClient.tsx` / `NewPackageFieldClient.tsx`
- Editing `applyDefaultRoleFilter` or `userTypeToContext` in
  `app/api/policies/[id]/premiums/route.ts`
- Editing `isPremiumPkg` in any field editor
- Editing `USER_TYPE_LABELS` (`AuditLogPanel.tsx`),
  `SYNTHETIC_FIELDS_BY_SOURCE` / `PACKAGE_COLOR_MAP` /
  `BUILT_IN_SECTION_TEMPLATES` (`PdfTemplateEditor.tsx`),
  `SOURCES` / `FORMATS` / `SOURCE_COLORS` (`FieldResolverDiagPanel.tsx`)
- Adding a new schema column in `db/schema/premiums.ts` (Levy,
  Stamp Duty, Discount, etc.) â€” these are HK-only; the proper
  pattern is a tenant-scoped registry, not a global column
- Reviewing a PR that introduces a new `const FOO_OPTIONS = [ ... ]`
  or `const FOO_BY_X: Record<string, string> = { ... }` in
  `components/admin/**`, `app/api/**`, or `lib/**`
- Adding a new `user.userType === "X"` branch where the rule should
  be admin-configurable
- Diagnosing "admin can't add a new role / context / column" /
  "tenant X needs a different list of premium roles" / "Levy column
  shouldn't be there for non-HK tenant"

## The 30-second cheatsheet

| Concern | Pattern | Don't do |
|---|---|---|
| New dropdown in an admin editor | Read from `form_options` group | `const FOO_OPTIONS = [ ... ]` in the component |
| New role / context / status / package type | New `form_options` group_key + admin UI to edit it | Hardcode in code; admins can't change it |
| Branch on a config value | Use `meta.<semanticTag>` (e.g. `meta.premiumRole`, `meta.isPremium`) | `label.includes("client")` / `key === "main"` |
| Map DB column â†’ suggested role | `meta.suggestedColumns[]` on the role row in `form_options.premium_roles` | `Record<string, string>` duplicated across files |
| "Is this a premium package?" | `package.meta.isPremium` | `key === "premiumRecord" \|\| key === "accounting"` |
| Role-based visibility | `form_options.user_type_visibility.meta.allowedPremiumRoles` + per-field `meta.visibleToRoles` override | Hardcoded `if (userType === "client" && role === "net")` |
| HK-specific columns (Levy / Stamp Duty / Discount) | Tag locale in registry; tenant-scoped `form_options` decide visibility | Schema-level columns assumed to apply to every tenant |
| Adding "one more" entry to an existing hardcoded list | Migrate the list to `form_options` first, THEN add the entry | Grow the violation |

